Honoring the Senior Class of 2020

KSN and KODE have launched a new initiative to recognize Seniors of the Class of 2020. This initiative will be hosted at
https://www.fourstateshomepage.com/class-of-2020-photo-submission/ and is free to all seniors to participate in. Seniors and their families may upload a picture with information about the student to the site.

This virtual graduation/recognition page will be promoted on television and in news broadcasts and is being provided as a way to recognize the seniors who have not been able to participate in normal senior festivities.

shared_text:
Heidi Boyer is with Natalie Renfro and 4 others.
March 26 at 4:31 PM ·

4,430 meals went out to our community today!
It’s been an honor to be able to serve our students and community during this time, the best way we know how...by feeding you 🥰
It’s our hope that the meals you receive are a blessing in some way, whether it is helping lift a financial burden or keeping you home and not having to make a trip to the grocery store 🙂
I don’t know about y’all but going to Walmart lately gives me anxiety and triggers OCD hand washing episodes I never knew I had 🧼💦 😂

We hope you are happy, healthy and safe.
We MISS everyone’s smiling faces!

Seneca Elementary School Seneca,MO
March 19 at 2:38 PM ·

Update: Due to some availability and distribution issues we will not be able to deliver meals a week at a time. Rather, we will have biweekly delivery and pick up.

Friday, March 20th meal distribution will include food for the weekend as well! Please remember if you would like to keep receiving, or start receiving meals to go to the NEW form and add your info. The form was posted on both our page and our district page yesterday. Starting Monday March 23rd we will be offering delivery (at drop points) and pick up twice a week. Monday’s meal will include lunch and breakfast for Monday - Thursday breakfast. Thursday’s pick up will include meals for Thursday lunch - Monday breakfast. Please take advantage of this great program!

Breakfast-
Mini Blueberry Waffle
Banana
Milk

Lunch-
Cheese Sticks
Chex-Mix
Fresh Fruit
Milk

Weekend-
2 uncrustables
1 Cereal
1 Juice
2 Fruit
2 Carrot Sticks
3 Milks

post_text:
Congratulations!!

Eleven students represented Seneca at last weekend's All-District and All-Conference Honor Band event. Seven of the eleven auditioned and were accepted into the All-District Band (comprised of about 25 school from our region of Missouri) and four of the students were nominated and accepted into the Conference Band. They all worked for about 12 hours between Friday and Saturday and put on a concert Saturday afternoon.

From Left to right in the picture:(back row) Wilson DePriest, Silas Hauser, Logan Williams, Jason Smith, Jase Cornett, Aaron Ramsey, Samantha Mack, Kaleila Uto. (Front row): Katelyn Connell, Olivia Clark. Not Pictured: Emma Hawkins.

Seneca R-7 Schools Foundation
September 30, 2018 at 5:13 PM ·

Seneca alumni! We decided last year at a Foundation meeting that we were going to try to make a database of all alumni including addresses and email addresses. We would like to send invites to our banquet and possibly some day start sending annual updates about what is going on in our district. We will not give this information out and we will not send mail very often. I have been working on the database for several months and now need your information. If you would, please message me or this page your name, maiden name, address, email address and the year your graduated, it would be greatly appreciated! Thank you!
Staci Conduff Cooper, Class of '87

post_text: NOTICE: After returning from checking on any flooding at the ball fields, I was informed that public works personnel had contacted SRO Kelly to inform him that the low-water bridges were being closed around town. Mr. Smith is out checking on other places where water may prohibit our bus traffic. The good news is, any freezing precipitation appears to be coming after the afternoon bus routes. This notice is simply to provide a heads-up for parents coming to campus and those with bus riders that there may be some delays due to rerouting. Stay dry and safe!

post_text: I would like to share a situation that occurred in the elementary today. A survey, prepared by one of our cadet teachers for a high school class, was given in one of our 3rd grade classes. It is our practice to review such surveys prior to administration. This one was not. Questions on the survey were not appropriate for the age. As an education community, we support research and helping other students and teachers; however, questions should always be screened. Mrs. Eidson has attempted to contact each student's parent that was given the survey. We apologize that the questions were not reviewed and are reviewing what we can do to avoid this in the future.

post_text: We will be in school tomorrow, May 2! Thanks to the City for the OK to come back. Please be patient on bus routes, as it may take a bit longer to navigate the roads. As of this moment, Condor is the only road we will not be able to make our stops. As for a makeup day, we are making a formal request to the Department of Elementary and Secondary Education for forgiveness of the day missed. If approved, May 19 will remain the last day. If denied, the last day will be May 22. I'm feeling a great deal of pressure to get this letter right🙂!

People seem to be focusing on what the bond proposal will do the first year; how about talking about what it will do the coming years? $350,000 a year freed up, imagine the possibilities.
